      "narrative": "TrustDB's WAF of 3.04 is between LMDB (1x, no compaction) and RocksDB (10–30x in compaction-heavy workloads). The B-ε tree design gives better write amplification than LSM trees at the cost of slightly worse read amplification. The standout metric: governance overhead at 3.3% vs 163% for app-layer enforcement. This means TrustDB's built-in confidence tracking, provenance, and temporal decay cost 49x less than bolting the same capabilities onto a traditional database. The NVM layer adds two-region mmap for LPDDR5X PASR bank idling (15–25mW idle savings), a per-thread write coalescer achieving 8–10x fewer CAS operations, and adaptive config switching that delivers 41x range scan improvement while trading only 35% on point lookups. mmap hints (THP, MADV_RANDOM, prefault) further optimize memory access patterns.",
