      "narrative": "This is TrustDB's most dramatic advantage. On Apple Silicon, QoS-based E-core pinning achieves 9.1x lower CPU power than SQLite WAL+NORMAL at comparable durability. The incremental power cost (delta over idle) is 24.8x lower. No competitor database has explicit Apple Silicon QoS integration — SQLite, RocksDB, and Core Data all run on whatever cores the OS scheduler assigns. This makes TrustDB uniquely viable for always-on edge/IoT deployments and extends battery life on laptops/phones. The NVM persistence engine extends this advantage dramatically: Tier 1 dc cvap flushes cost ~0mW in storage I/O (CPU cache to DRAM only), while epoch batching via LPSR preservation delivers a 3,000x storage energy reduction by keeping NVMe asleep. The BatteryStateMonitor adapts Tier 2 intervals from 5ms (charging) to infinity (Low Power Mode disabled), and confidence-weighted persistence keeps speculative data in DRAM only.",
